HEADWORD: Scopuliped
<hw>Scop"u*li*ped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scopulae</ets>, pl., a little broom (fr. <ets>scopae</ets> a broom)
+ <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any species of bee which has on the hind legs a brush of hairs used
for collecting pollen, as the hive bees and bumblebees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scopulous</ent>⟦br⟧
